      "id": "9adffdf1_3af1536b",
      "file_path": "sources/hv-collector-utils/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/dcae/collectors/veshv/utils/logging/LogLevel.kt",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 32,
      "message": "1. Let's add `.toUpperCase()` to be more flexible\n2. Rename function to `fromString` - it's more natural to call LogLevel.fromString than LogLevel.getLogLevel (this looks like singleton call)\n3. I'm not sure we want to simply catch this exception and provide \ndefault - it might be useful to log this information somewhere.\nWe can use Option for this:\n```\n        fun optionFromString(level: String) = Try {\n            valueOf(level.toUpperCase())\n        }.toOption()\n```\n```ArgVesHvConfiguration\n\nlogLevel = determineLoglevel(logLevel)\n\n    private fun determineLoglevel(logLevel: String) = LogLevel.optionFromString(logLevel)\n            .getOrElse {\n                logger.warn {\n                    \"Failed to parse $logLevel as $LOG_LEVEL command line. \" +\n                            \"Using default log level (${LogLevel.INFO})\"\n                }\n                LogLevel.INFO\n            }\n```\nI'm not convinced it's nice solution but at least we get log message :)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3701,
        "name": "Filip Krzywka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "filip.krzywka@nokia.com",
        "username": "fkrzywka"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-19 08:57:31.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_5af69764",
      "file_path": "sources/hv-collector-utils/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/dcae/collectors/veshv/utils/logging/Logger.kt",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "`.level = level.level`\nMaybe it's just me, but looks weird :) \n\nNot really insisting, but consider renaming `level` property to `logbackLevel` and maybe add `invoke` function to LogLevel and make property private.\n\n```.level = level.logbackLevel```\n```.level = level()\n\n    operator fun invoke() = logbackLevel\n```",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3701,
        "name": "Filip Krzywka",
